# Sardis Open Core License

## 1. Open Source Components (MIT License)

The following components of Sardis are licensed under the **MIT License**:
- `packages/sardis-sdk/`
- `packages/sardis-mcp-server/`
- `packages/sardis-cli/`

---

## 2. Proprietary Core Components

The following core infrastructure components remain **Proprietary** and are the exclusive property of Efe Baran Durmaz:
- `packages/sardis-core/` (Internal Policy Engine logic, Database schemas)
- `packages/sardis-chain/` (MPC Signing Node management, Key threshold logic)
- `packages/sardis-compliance/` (Direct integration logic for Persona/Elliptic)
- `packages/sardis-api/` (Centralized API routing and orchestration)

---

## 3. Why Open Core?
We believe the **Agent Economy** needs an open standard. By open-sourcing our SDKs and MCP connectors, we allow developers to integrate Sardis with any agent framework securely. We protect our core infrastructure to ensure the long-term sustainability and security of the protocol.

